"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475626","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-21","<p>The UK is currently working with the European Commission and other Member States to agree the technical approach to be taken to implementation of these Articles.</p><p> </p><p>Consultation will take place once the details of the approach have been agreed at EU level.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475626/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T15:43:09.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475626/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475626/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-15","Tobacco: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to consult on the transposition of Articles 15 and 16 of the European Tobacco Products Directorate into UK law.","false","Biography information for Hannah Bardell","Livingston","Hannah Bardell","31263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475628","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-23","<p>Council treasurers will need to certify that the additional revenue will be used to fund adult social care. The Secretary of State will review the arrangements each year as part of the process for setting referendum principles. These are approved by the House of Commons each year and will take into account the way councils have used the additional flexibility when doing so.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475628/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-23T17:00:11.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475628/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475628/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-15","Social Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has put measures in place to ensure that funding raised through the two per cent precept levied by local government will be spent on adult social care.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","31224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475629","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-04-26","<p>The Government submitted an initial UK application to the EU Solidarity Fund on Friday 26 February. The application included an estimate of eligible costs from Scotland, Wales, Cumbria, Lancashire, Greater Manchester, North Yorkshire and the City of York, West Yorkshire, and Northumberland.</p><p>Having made this initial application, we are in the process of refining our cost estimations and figures, and will work with the Commission to finalise details.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475629/answer",,,,,,"2016-04-26T14:46:50.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475629/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475629/answer","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475629/answer/previousversion/52527","Biography information for James Wharton","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Floods: European Union Solidarity Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, which areas of the UK are covered by his Department's application for assistance from the EU Solidarity Fund to help communities affected by recent floods.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","31225"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475630","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Department encourages local authorities to be open and transparent with their data. The Local Audit and Accountability Act 2014 requires local authorities to publish their audited accounts on their website, and the Local Government Transparency Code 2015 requires local authorities to publish details of expenditure, resource and assets, including details of all of their contracts with a value of over £5,000.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475630/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T17:10:55.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475630/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475630/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Local Government: Public Private Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29831, what recent steps he has taken to encourage all local authorities to publish (a) transparent financial audits and (b) undisclosed procurement costs for all public-private contracts.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475632","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Department does not provide any formal guidance.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475632/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T17:09:40.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475632/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475632/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Local Government: Public Private Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29830, what guidance his Department provides to local authorities on improving coordination between support teams when some or all of those services are outsourced.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475633","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-04-26","<p>The Government submitted an initial UK application to the EU Solidarity Fund on Friday 26 February. The application included an estimate of eligible costs from Scotland, Wales, Cumbria, Lancashire, Greater Manchester, North Yorkshire and the City of York, West Yorkshire, and Northumberland.</p><p>Having made this initial application, we are in the process of refining our cost estimations and figures, and will work with the Commission to finalise details.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475633/answer",,,,,,"2016-04-26T14:46:50.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475633/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475633/answer","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475633/answer/previousversion/52528","Biography information for James Wharton","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Floods: European Union Solidarity Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, on what date an application was submitted for assistance from the EU Solidarity Fund to help communities affected by recent floods.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","31267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475634","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Department does not provide any guidance.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475634/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T17:09:02.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475634/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475634/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Local Government: Public Private Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29830, what guidance his Department provides to local authorities on the procurement of public-private partnerships.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475636","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Government has committed to carry out the necessary research to understand what, if any, legislative changes regarding electrical safety checks in the private rented sector should be introduced.</p><p>Feedback on this research will be provided during the Lords Report stage of the Housing and Planning Bill.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475636/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T17:12:21.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475636/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475636/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Private Rented Housing: Electrical Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to introduce mandatory five yearly electrical safety checks in the private rented sector.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475637","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-23","<p>The Government is aware of concerns surrounding the financial threshold above which consultation on service charges must take place under section 20 of the Landlord and Tenant Act 1985 (as amended by the Commonhold and Leasehold Reform Act 2002). This was also referred to as part of the Competition and Markets Authority study into property management services. We have been working with stakeholders in the sector, including the Association of Residential Managing Agents, to consider what can be done to improve how section 20 works, including the financial threshold. The Government is awaiting the final set of recommendations from the Association and will respond to the Competition and Markets Authority study in the Autumn.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475637/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-23T17:32:03.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475637/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475637/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Service Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to increase the financial limit for the contribution of tenants to qualifying works as set out in paragraph 6 of the Service Charges (Consultation Requirements) (England) Regulations 2003.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","31083"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475638","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-09","<p>The total number of homes completed under the Get Britain Building programme from its launch in November 2011 to September 2015 is 9,761. Of these, 1400 are affordable homes.</p><p>Government does not collect data concerning the number of jobs created by the Get Britain Building programme.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475638/answer",,,,,,"2016-05-09T15:41:37.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475638/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475638/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many (a) homes and (b) affordable homes have been completed under the Get Britain Building scheme to date; and what estimate he has made of the number of new jobs created by that scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","31113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475639","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-22","<p>The Department does not require local authorities to submit data on the nationality of rough sleepers. However information on the nationality of rough sleepers in London, collected by the Combined Homelessness and Information Network, is shown in the Department’s annual rough sleeping statistical release which is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/503015/Rough_Sleeping_Autumn_2015_statistical_release.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/503015/Rough_Sleeping_Autumn_2015_statistical_release.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475639/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T16:53:02.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475639/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475639/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-15","Sleeping Rough","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what statistics his Department holds on the nationality of people who are sleeping rough.","false","Biography information for David Mackintosh","Northampton South","David Mackintosh","31152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475641","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-21","<p>In March, the Government published ‘Enabling resilience in the water sector’ (see: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/water-sector-improving-long-term-resilience" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/water-sector-improving-long-term-resilience</a>) which sets out our expectation that sewerage companies will show leadership in working with the wide range of actors with an impact on drainage systems to assess future pressures and will undertake the necessary long-term planning and investment to meet their duties.</p><p>Under section 94 of the Water Industry Act 1991, a sewerage company has a duty to provide a sewerage service so as to effectually drain its area. This duty does not mean that sewerage companies must prevent sewer flooding in all circumstances as it would not be practicable to build sewers to a capacity necessary to cope with the additional load of extreme rainfall events.</p><p>Working in partnership with other risk management authorities, water companies also have a wider role to play in flood risk management including helping manage the risks associated with very heavy rainfall and flash flooding. They must exercise their flood risk management functions in a way which is consistent with national and local flood risk management strategies.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475641/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T15:24:58.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475641/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475641/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-03-15","Sewers: Rain","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will make it her policy to require utilities companies, highways authorities and developers to ensure that new drainage and sewerage systems have sufficient capacity to accommodate the rainfall volume experienced on 26 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","31076"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475642","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-21","<p>Since 1992 landscape maintenance and allied work in The Royal Parks (TRP) has been contracted out, and there are no gardeners employed by the contractors that are eligible for the Principal Civil Service Pension Scheme (PCSPS) .</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475642/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T13:25:31.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475642/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475642/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-15","Royal Parks: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether the gardeners employed by the Royal Parks are enrolled in the civil service pension scheme; and how many such gardeners are enrolled in each version of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","31132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475643","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-21","<p>Government continually assesses the resilience of the communications network and works closely with the communications industry to do this. Power is the main dependency of the communications sector, and the Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR), published in November 2015, highlighted Government’s commitment to enhancing the UK’s resilience to power disruption. Government will continue to work with industry to ensure the ongoing resilience and availability of services across the sector in the event of power loss.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475643/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T10:12:07.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475643/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475643/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-15","Telecommunications: Power Failures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether he has made an assessment of the resilience of the (a) mobile telephone network, (b) landline telephone network and (c) fibre optic broadband network after a power cut; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","31181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475645","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>As you know, I am committed to review all claims of civilian casualties, which we take very seriously. The Ministry of Defence has robust processes in place to review reports of alleged incidents. An assessment is carried out after every British strike; we determine the scale of the damage that has been caused and review very carefully whether there are likely to have been civilian casualties. Investigations are launched where appropriate.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475645/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T16:03:32.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475645/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475645/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Middle East: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department has established a civilian casualties tracking cell to investigate reports of alleged incidents involving RAF aeroplanes in Syria and Iraq.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","31187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475646","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>As part of last year's Strategic Defence and Security Review, we conducted a comprehensive assessment of our future capability requirements including for combat air. Within this, we looked at what could be provided by current and planned capabilities including Protector. The next phase of our collaboration on Unmanned Combat Air Systems with France will mature advanced technologies to inform future acquisition choices.</p><p>As part of last year's Strategic Defence and Security Review, we conducted a comprehensive assessment of our future capability requirements including for combat air. Within this, we looked at what could be provided by current and planned capabilities including Protector. The next phase of our collaboration on Unmanned Combat Air Systems with France is looking at capability need beyond Protector and so will mature advanced technologies to develop operational demonstrators.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475646/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T17:50:21.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475646/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475646/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","France: Military Alliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment of the merits of the Protector drone and other current and projected UK capability requirements was made to underpin the recent £1.5 billion UK-France collaboration on a joint unmanned combat air vehicle.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","31168"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475647","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-23","<p>Since the start of the 2015-16 session of Parliament to 17 March 2016, 47 written parliamentary questions (PQs) tabled to the Ministry of Defence (MOD) were not answered because disclosure would have been likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness, or security of our Armed Forces or Allies. This figure represents 2% of the total number of 2,318 PQs answered by the MOD during that period.</p><p>In 19 further PQs, only part of the answer was withheld so as to protect the capability, effectiveness, or security of our Armed Forces or Allies.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475647/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-23T16:26:01.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475647/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475647/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Ministry of Defence: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions his Department has not provided substantive answers to written parliamentary questions by stating that disclosure of the information would likely prejudice the capability, effectiveness, or security of our Armed Forces or Allies in this parliamentary session.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","31197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475649","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>International Humanitarian Law is founded in customary international law but now extensively codified in international agreements, most notably the Geneva Conventions of 1949 and the Additional Protocols. The UK's interpretation of the principles of proportionality, military necessity, humanity and distinction is set out in the Ministry of Defence's Joint Service Publication (JSP) 383, the Manual of the Law of Armed Conflict, which is available online (https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jsp-383).</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475649/answer",,,,,"31213 ; 31214 ; 31215","2016-03-21T15:55:15.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475649/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475649/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","International Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29390, what definition of principle of proportionality his Department uses to assess whether an incident counts as a violation of international humanitarian law.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","31216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475650","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>International Humanitarian Law is founded in customary international law but now extensively codified in international agreements, most notably the Geneva Conventions of 1949 and the Additional Protocols. The UK's interpretation of the principles of proportionality, military necessity, humanity and distinction is set out in the Ministry of Defence's Joint Service Publication (JSP) 383, the Manual of the Law of Armed Conflict, which is available online (https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jsp-383).</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475650/answer",,,,,"31214 ; 31215 ; 31216","2016-03-21T15:55:15.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475650/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475650/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","International Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29390, what definition of principle of military necessity his Department uses to assess whether an incident counts as violation of international humanitarian law.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","31213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475651","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>International Humanitarian Law is founded in customary international law but now extensively codified in international agreements, most notably the Geneva Conventions of 1949 and the Additional Protocols. The UK's interpretation of the principles of proportionality, military necessity, humanity and distinction is set out in the Ministry of Defence's Joint Service Publication (JSP) 383, the Manual of the Law of Armed Conflict, which is available online (https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jsp-383).</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475651/answer",,,,,"31213 ; 31215 ; 31216","2016-03-21T15:55:16.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475651/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475651/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","International Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29390, what definition of principle of humanity his Department uses to assess whether an incident counts as a violation of international humanitarian law.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","31214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475652","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>International Humanitarian Law is founded in customary international law but now extensively codified in international agreements, most notably the Geneva Conventions of 1949 and the Additional Protocols. The UK's interpretation of the principles of proportionality, military necessity, humanity and distinction is set out in the Ministry of Defence's Joint Service Publication (JSP) 383, the Manual of the Law of Armed Conflict, which is available online (https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jsp-383).</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475652/answer",,,,,"31213 ; 31214 ; 31216","2016-03-21T15:55:16.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475652/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475652/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","International Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29390, what definition of principle of distinction his Department uses to assess whether an incident counts as a violation of international humanitarian law.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","31215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475654","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-23","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review reaffirmed the UK's commitment to providing contributions to NATO, UN, and EU operations and exercises. However, the MOD does not hold the information in the format requested and it could be provided only at disproportionate cost<em>.</em></p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475654/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-23T16:27:16.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475654/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475654/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of UK military personnel have been deployed on (a) NATO, (b) UN and (c) EU-coordinated operations and training over the lpast 10 years.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","31189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475655","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-23","<p>Ministers answer Parliamentary Questions in accordance with the Ministerial Code which states that:</p><p>&quot;Ministers should be as open as possible with Parliament and the public, refusing to provide information only when disclosure would not be in the public interest, which should be decided in accordance with the relevant statutes and the <em>Freedom of Information Act 2000&quot;. </em></p><p>In addition, Parliamentary Questions may not receive a substantive answer if the information requested is not held, if providing the answer to a written question would incur disproportionate cost, if the answer contains personal or confidential information which is not appropriate for publication or if it is not possible to respond in the time available before prorogation.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475655/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-23T16:27:54.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475655/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475655/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Ministry of Defence: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons his Department will not give a substantive answer to Parliamentary questions.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","31211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475656","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-17","<p>The estimated economic benefit of British Forces Cyprus and the Sovereign Base Areas Administration to the Republic of Cyprus (RoC) economy was assessed in 2015 to be approximately 1% of RoC Gross Domestic Product.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475656/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:24:23.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475656/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475656/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Cyprus: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate how much the presence of the UK military in Cyprus contributes annually to the Cypriot economy.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","31138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475658","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>All widow(er)s of serving members of the Armed Forces are sent a letter of condolence and a comprehensive Bereavement Pack which is tailored to their family circumstances and provides full details of the support available to them.</p><p>When Veterans UK are notified of the death of a Veteran the Veterans Welfare Service send a leaflet to the widow(er) detailing support groups. The Veterans Welfare Service also visit and assist in accessing further support.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475658/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T16:41:54.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475658/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475658/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","War Widows","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to notify war widows and widowers of support groups they can access.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","31151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475659","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Department takes a number of steps each year, with assistance from the Electoral Commission, to inform Service personnel of the arrangements for electoral registration. The annual information campaign encouraging Service personnel and their families to register to vote was launched on 1 February 2016, in conjunction with the National Voter Registration Drive. We will issue an updated, separate instruction for the EU Referendum and conduct further internal communications to once again encourage Service personnel to register to vote.</p><p> </p><p>Registration is a personal matter and personnel are free to choose whether and, how they register to vote. Our information campaign encourages personnel to consider applying to vote by proxy if they are serving in a location where postal services may be difficult.</p><p>The number of Service personnel who are registered to vote was published in the 2015 Armed Forces Continuous Attitude Survey (AFCAS) Annex B, Table B22.1-3, available on the gov.uk website at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/428636/20150520_afcas_15_annex_b_ref_tables.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/428636/20150520_afcas_15_annex_b_ref_tables.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The Department does not hold information on how personnel choose to cast their vote, be that in person, by post, or by proxy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475659/answer",,,,,"31073 ; 31074","2016-03-21T17:38:31.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475659/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475659/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will take steps to maximise the participation of service personnel in the forthcoming EU referendum; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","Wycombe","Steve Baker","31072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475660","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Written Ministerial Statement I made on 10 March 2016, (Official Report, column WS605).</p><p>A programme of works has been developed to deliver the improved infrastructure and accommodation at Volunteer Gliding Squadrons. Work also continues to align and integrate the various training courses for Air Cadets into an integrated aviation training package. In future this will be tailored to a cadet's level of experience and will cover aviation related ground training, realistic flight simulation with part-task training glider simulators, and formal gliding instruction on Volunteer Gliding Squadrons.</p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475660/answer","Hansard Extract  10 March 2016 WMS.docx","Hansard Extract  10 March 2016 WMS.docx","Air Cadet Aviation Relaunch","Air Cadet Aviation Relaunch",,"2016-03-21T15:56:15.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475660/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475660/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Air Cadet Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress his Department has made on the restructuring process set out in the review of the Air Cadet Organisation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475662","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>Total running costs of the Air Cadet Organisation including service and civilian manpower but excluding the annual works programme and contracted services was:</p><p>£23.8 million in Financial Year (FY) 2011-12</p><p>£22.0 million in FY 2012-13</p><p>£23.1 million in FY 2013-14</p><p>£24.5 million in FY 2014-15</p><p>The estimated outturn in FY 2015-16 is £25.7 million.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475662/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T15:56:44.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475662/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475662/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Air Cadet Organisation: Operating Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate his Department has made of the running costs of the Air Cadet Organisation in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31098"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475663","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Air Cadet Organisation (ACO) is manned primarily by Cadet Force Adult Volunteer staff. The small permanently staffed Headquarters Air Cadets (HQ AC), alongside Headquarters 2 Flying Training School (HQ 2FTS) and the regional and wing formations, together have a staff of approximately 250 personnel.</p><p>Glider maintenance and recovery is undertaken by contractors and it is their responsibility for the manning of the contracted work.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475663/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T15:54:15.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475663/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475663/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Air Cadet Organisation: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate his Department has made of the number of staff it has hired to support the Air Cadet Organisation in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475664","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>Following the Written Ministerial Statement I released on 10 March 2016, (Official Report, column WS605) concerning the Air Cadet Aviation Relaunch, we have received a range of representations from Cadet Force Adult Volunteer staff of the mainstream Air Cadets and the Volunteer Gliding Squadrons. This includes representations through their direct chain of command.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475664/answer","Hansard Extract  10 March 2016 WMS.docx","Hansard Extract  10 March 2016 WMS.docx","Air Cadet Aviation Relaunch","Air Cadet Aviation Relaunch",,"2016-03-21T15:57:23.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475664/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475664/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Air Cadet Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what representations he has received from volunteer representatives of the Air Cadet Organisation on the review of the Air Cadet Organisation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475666","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>The information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost. The capitalisation threshold to be recorded on an asset register is £25,000, so assets held which do not meet that threshold will only appear on unit inventories across the entire Air Cadet Organisation</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475666/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T16:50:07.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475666/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/475666/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-15","Air Cadet Organisation: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate his Department has made of the value of the assets held by the Air Cadet Organisation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31090"
