"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470362","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-22","<p>While there are no VAT reliefs for the construction of memorials, the Government operates a grant refund scheme for refunding some or all of the VAT costs involved in the construction, repair and maintenance of certain memorials. Further details of the scheme and application for a refund should be made to the Department of Culture, Media and Sport.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470362/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T17:39:41.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470362/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470362/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-14","Monuments: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy to exempt the proposed Oaks Colliery Memorial from the requirement to pay VAT on its construction and installation.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","30890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470363","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-17","<p>There are higher duty rates on both beer and cider above 7.5 per cent alcohol by volume compared to standard strength beers and ciders. This is to encourage the production and consumption of lower strength products.</p><p> </p><p>The Chancellor keeps all duty rates under review as part of the Budget process.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470363/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T17:54:31.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470363/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470363/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-14","Alcoholic Drinks: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the reasons are for the difference between the duty imposed on cider with alcohol content of 7.5 per cent and beer with a similar alcohol content.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","30978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470364","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-17","<p>For the 2013-14 tax year (the latest tax year for which information is available), there were 118,000 non-domiciled individuals who completed a Self-Assessment return (rounded to the nearest 100).</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470364/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T17:30:42.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470364/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470364/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-14","Taxation: Domicil","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 3 March 2016 to Question 29027, how many people currently have non-domicile tax status.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","30975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470365","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-17","<p>It is not anticipated that HM Revenue and Customs’ (HMRC) withdrawal of some valuation services will impact the take up of employee ownership schemes.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC has announced the withdrawal of income tax and PAYE post-transaction valuation checks, but has not withdrawn those valuation services that are most relevant to employee ownership schemes. These consist of:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Enterprise Management Incentives (EMI),</p></li><li><p>Company Share Option Plans (CSOP),</p></li><li><p>Save As You Earn share option schemes (SAYE),</p></li><li><p>Share Incentive Plans (SIP) and</p></li><li><p>Employee Shareholder Status (ESS).</p><p> </p><p>HMRC has, however, announced a review of the valuation services for those schemes and is consulting interested parties. Most people submit acceptable valuations in respect of these schemes, and HMRC is therefore considering whether the valuation service offered continues to be needed.</p><p> </p></li></ul>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470365/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T17:28:51.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470365/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470365/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-14","Employee Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on employee ownership schemes of the decision by HM Revenue and Customs to withdraw its valuation check service; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","31012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470366","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-12","<p>The Treasury has conducted internal studies to examine how far and how quickly the benefits of oil and gas price falls were fed through to consumers, and engaged with industry to stress the importance of this happening. These were internal studies used to inform government policy on energy markets and were not intended for publication. The government continues to monitor the market.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470366/answer",,,,,,"2016-04-12T13:52:05.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470366/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470366/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-14","Natural Gas: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he plans to publish the results of his Department's investigation into benefits to consumers from falling gas prices.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","30996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470367","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-12","<p>The Treasury has conducted internal studies to examine how far and how quickly the benefits of oil and gas price falls were fed through to consumers, and engaged with industry to stress the importance of this happening. The Government welcomes the CMA’s provisional decisions on remedies of their energy market investigation, which included proposals to introduce a safeguard tariff to protect customers on pre-payment meters. The government will act quickly on the CMA’s recommendations to ensure that bill payers get a fair deal from energy markets.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470367/answer",,,,,,"2016-04-12T13:40:52.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470367/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470367/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-14","Natural Gas: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Competition and Markets Authority report on energy market investigation published on 10 March 2016, what recent progress has been made on his Department's investigation into consumer benefits from falling gas prices.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","31035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470368","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-22","<p>HM Treasury does not receive any UK funding from this programme, which is instead administered by other government departments.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470368/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T17:43:05.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470368/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470368/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-14","European Social Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department received from the European Social Fund between (a) 2007 and 2014 and (b) 2014 and the last month for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","31048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470370","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-24","<p>The Department’s annual Local Authority’s Housing Statistics provide information on the total households on local authority waiting lists in England but do not record nationality. The Department’s English Housing Survey does ask whether respondents are on a waiting list and also records nationality. The sample size, however, is not sufficient to provide a robust estimate by nationality.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470370/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-24T16:30:13.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470370/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470370/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-14","Social Rented Housing: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of nationals from other EU member states who are on social housing waiting lists in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","31038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470371","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-17","<p>Since 2010 we have enabled local authorities to help prevent or relieve over one million cases of homelessness. But one person without a home is one too many. So we have increased central funding for homelessness to £139 million over the next four years, and protected the homelessness prevention funding to councils amounting to £315 million by 2020.</p><p>Statistics for each of the last five years on statutory homelessness acceptances, homelessness prevention and relief and rough sleeping are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics</a></p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470371/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:40:10.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470371/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470371/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-14","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of the level of homelessness in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470372","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-17","<p>The Department takes a flexible approach to deploying officials across priorities. We continuously keep this under review to ensure that we are providing the best possible response to critical policy areas.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470372/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:39:10.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470372/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470372/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-14","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many officials of his Department are working full-time on strategies to tackle homelessness; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470373","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-17","<p>Statistics on statutory homelessness acceptances for the last 12 months are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness</a></p><p>Table 780 gives information on household type, table 781 gives information on the age of applicants, and tables 785 and 786 give details on applications from foreign nationals.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470373/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:38:23.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470373/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470373/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-14","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many of which (a) age (b) sex and (c) nationality were homeless in the last 12 months; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470374","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-17","<p>Since 2010 we have invested over £500 million to enable local authorities and the voluntary sector to support those vulnerable and at risk of homelessness.</p><p>One person without a home is one too many and we are committed to do all we can to prevent homelessness. We have protected the homelessness prevention funding local authorities receive, totalling £315 million by 2019-20. This builds on our Spending Review commitment to increase central government funding to £139 million over the next four years. We will work with homelessness organisations to consider other options, including legislation, to ensure those at risk of homelessness get earlier and more effective support.</p><p>We also announced in the Budget £100 million to deliver low cost ‘move on’ accommodation to enable people leaving hostels and refuges to make a sustainable recovery from a homelessness crisis, providing at least 2,000 places for vulnerable people to enable independent living.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470374/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:37:20.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470374/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470374/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-14","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department has spent on reducing homelessness in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","30970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470375","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-22","<p>Defra and the Department for Communities and Local Government (DCLG) are working in partnership to develop a National Litter Strategy. To help us, we have set up a Litter Strategy Advisory Group which includes representatives from local government, campaign groups and independent experts, as well as the packaging and fast-food industries. Other relevant Departments, such as Department for Transport, Department of Health, Home Office or Ministry of Justice will attend the Advisory Group as appropriate. Ministers from both Defra and DCLG attended an initial meeting of key stakeholders with an interest in this issue and are taking an active interest in the work of the Group. Officials from Defra and DCLG are of course in close contact on litter policy.</p><p> </p><p>The National Litter Strategy will complement existing work including actions to address litter in the marine environment. It will promote concerted, co-ordinated and effective actions to reduce litter and littering on land, which in turn should lead to a reduction in the amount of litter reaching the marine environment.</p><p> </p><p>The UK’s Marine Strategy sets out the actions we are taking to improve the marine environment, including what we are doing to tackle marine litter. The Strategy is approved by the Government and the Devolved Administrations. At an official level, development of the Strategy is overseen by a steering group made up of relevant officials from Defra, Defra Group partners and other relevant Government Departments. This is supported by our Clean and Safe Seas Evidence Group that includes a specific sub-group on marine litter. In addition, given the trans-boundary nature of marine litter, we work closely with other countries sharing our seas through an EU-level Technical Group on Marine Litter and an Oslo and Paris Convention for the Protection of the Marine Environment of the North East Atlantic (OSPAR) group on marine litter.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470375/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T14:52:09.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470375/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470375/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-03-14","Litter: Departmental Coordination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what cross-departmental working groups or structures are in place in respect of (a) litter policy and (b) marine litter at (i) official and (ii) ministerial level.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","30918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470377","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-29","<p>A response was sent on 17 March.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470377/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-29T11:22:50.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470377/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470377/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-14","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to respond to the letter from the hon. Member for Wolverhampton South West of 27 January 2016 on the local government finance settlement.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","30886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470378","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-21","<p>The legal requirements for publicising planning applications are set out in Article 15 of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure)(England) Order 2015.</p><p>Where advertisement in a local newspaper is required, the notice must be published in a newspaper circulating in the locality in which the land to which the application relates is situated<strong>.</strong></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470378/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T17:11:43.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470378/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470378/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-14","Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department issues to local authorities on determining the appropriate local media outlets for publication of planning notices with respect to those outlets' geographical coverage.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","30888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470379","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-22","<p>Ministers meet with representatives of local authorities, voluntary and charity sector organisations and other partners on a regular basis to discuss a range of issues including ways to improve support to help those who are vulnerable and at risk of becoming homeless.</p><p>In particular, I have chaired two roundtables with the chief executives of leading homelessness charities to help shape and inform our future approach to reducing homelessness.</p><p>I have also visited or met with representatives from the following homelessness organisations:</p><p>Connections St Martin’s in the Field <br>Arlington Hostel<br>The Passage<br>Crisis<br>Homeless Link<br>Thames Reach<br>St Mungo’s Broadway<br>Depaul<br>Riverside St George’s Support Centre<br>St Petroc's Society, Cornwall<br>St Basil's, Birmingham</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470379/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T17:51:06.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470379/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470379/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-14","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what representations he has received from homelessness charities in each of the last 12 months; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","30906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470380","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-18","<p>Romford h​as enjoyed record levels of funding over ​recent years - £332,259 in 2014/15; and £402,919 in 2015/16 (year to date ​14​th March).</p><p><br>​T​his investment from Arts Council England has supported a number of exciting projects, including​ ​the African Culture​,​ Arts and Sport Network​ and​ D-Live! delivered by Young Droots Theatre which aims to find a new generation of deaf artists and performers.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470380/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-18T14:43:17.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470380/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470380/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-14","Arts: Romford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much funding his Department has allocated to arts groups in Romford in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","30904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470382","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Anniversary of the sailing of the Mayflower is a wonderful opportunity to reignite the interest that American citizens have in our nations' shared history.</p><p>​ ​</p><p>Plymouth City Council are leading the commemorations for this anniversary - representing the beginning of one of the most enduring alliances in the world. The Government has made over £500,000 available to support the Council's ambition for this celebration to be a year of both national and international significance for the city.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470382/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T15:35:56.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470382/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470382/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-14","Mayflower: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans his Department has to commemorate the 400th anniversary of the 1620 voyage of the Mayflower.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","30909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470383","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-17","<p>The Government remains committed to diversity in the film and television industries. Viewers at home and abroad want to see their culture and diversity represented on television. The Government recognises the important contribution it makes to the overall success of international sales and revenue, which came to more than £2 billion in 2014.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470383/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T14:00:53.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470383/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470383/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-14","Film and Television: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 3 March 2016 to Question 28851, what assessment he has made of the potential benefit to international sales of British content of the commissioning of content with diverse voices.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","30991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470384","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-17","<p>The UK's selection competition for the title of 2023 European Capital of Culture is due to be launched before the end of 2016. The DCMS will consider how best to support potential bidders over the coming months.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470384/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T14:04:32.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470384/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470384/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-14","European Capital of Culture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent steps he has taken to support UK cities considering a bid for the title of European Capital of Culture 2023.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","31009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470385","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Department remains committed to embodying a collision warning system on Typhoon as a priority. Two possible solutions are being formally assessed. Procurement timelines will be informed by this assessment and the subsequent Departmental approval process.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470385/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T16:02:59.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470385/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470385/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 7 March 2016 to Question 30090, what the timeline is for the procurement of a collision warning system for the Typhoon aircraft.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","30993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470387","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Ministry of Defence currently has a total of 49 military personnel based in Jordan.</p><p>There is one defence civilian personnel post in the British Embassy Amman for which the new incumbent will be in place in July 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470387/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T16:02:22.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470387/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470387/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Jordan: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) military and (b) civilian personnel from his Department are based in Jordan.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","30994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470388","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>As at 17 March 2016, there are 16 serving military and six civilian women deployed on UN missions. The Ministry of Defence (MOD) does not hold the historic information sought as military personnel deployed on operations are not recorded by gender.</p><p>The answer to Question 28161 did not include personnel deployed by other Government departments and was limited to those provided only by the MOD and the Stabilisation Unit. Details of civilian personnel deployed to the UN by other departments are not centrally held, nor does the MOD hold centralised records of Government employees working with UN agencies.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470388/answer",,,,,"31005 ; 31006","2016-03-21T16:01:46.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470388/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470388/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","United Nations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 March 2016 to Question 28161, how many (a) military and (b) civilian personnel are deployed to which UN agencies.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","31004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470389","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>As at 17 March 2016, there are 16 serving military and six civilian women deployed on UN missions. The Ministry of Defence (MOD) does not hold the historic information sought as military personnel deployed on operations are not recorded by gender.</p><p>The answer to Question 28161 did not include personnel deployed by other Government departments and was limited to those provided only by the MOD and the Stabilisation Unit. Details of civilian personnel deployed to the UN by other departments are not centrally held, nor does the MOD hold centralised records of Government employees working with UN agencies.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470389/answer",,,,,"31004 ; 31006","2016-03-21T16:01:46.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470389/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470389/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","United Nations: Peacekeeping Operations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 March 2016 to Question 28161, how many of the (a) military and (b) civilian personnel deployed on UN peacekeeping operations are women.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","31005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470390","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>As at 17 March 2016, there are 16 serving military and six civilian women deployed on UN missions. The Ministry of Defence (MOD) does not hold the historic information sought as military personnel deployed on operations are not recorded by gender.</p><p>The answer to Question 28161 did not include personnel deployed by other Government departments and was limited to those provided only by the MOD and the Stabilisation Unit. Details of civilian personnel deployed to the UN by other departments are not centrally held, nor does the MOD hold centralised records of Government employees working with UN agencies.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470390/answer",,,,,"31004 ; 31005","2016-03-21T16:01:47.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470390/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470390/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","United Nations: Peacekeeping Operations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 March 2016 to Question 28161, whether the numbers of civilian personnel provided in that Answer include personnel deployed by other government departments.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","31006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470391","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-17","<p>The UK complies with all of its international obligations. The UK is not obliged to consider any asylum claim made on UK flagged vessels, including those of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary and the Royal Navy, outside of the UK's territorial waters.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470391/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:23:09.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470391/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470391/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Asylum: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether people rescued by (a) Royal Fleet Auxiliary and (b) Royal Navy vessels are able to claim for asylum in the UK if flagged in international waters.","false","Biography information for Ms Gisela Stuart","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Ms Gisela Stuart","31045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470392","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>All military personnel on UN operations deploy with personal equipment. Over the last six years these have included UN operations in: Mali, South Sudan, Democratic Republic of Congo, Somalia and Tunisia. In addition, under the current Memorandum of Understanding with the UN for the mission in Cyprus (UNFICYP) the UK Ministry of Defence provides two ambulances and 30 sets of Public Order Equipment.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470392/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T15:57:54.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470392/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470392/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","United Nations: Peacekeeping Operations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what UK military equipment has been deployed on UN peacekeeping operations in each of the last six years; and on what operations that equipment has been so deployed.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","31007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470393","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>Across the UK, full consideration was given to the value of training opportunities, the revised geographic laydown and future volunteer opportunities for affected Volunteer Gliding Squadron (VGS) personnel.</p><p>Cadets from all Scottish cadet units will still have the opportunity to fly gliders, with an enlarged 661 VGS providing a regional hub. We also plan to increase Air Experience Flight fixed wing flying opportunities in Scotland in due course. The reorganisation of air cadet gliding will provide air cadets with a better overall opportunity, with the emphasis moving from air experience to flying training. It is anticipated that 661 VGS will remain at Kirknewton, although I cannot confirm this until the Ministry of Defence estate rationalisation concludes later in the year.</p><p>The reduced VGS footprint will allow resources to be focused on the remaining Squadrons. This will enable more suitable infrastructure to be built and maintained that supports the Air Cadet Organisation more fully. The key development across the estate over time will be to provide new overnight accommodation and training facilities that safely allows cadets and adult instructors over full residential weekends to carry out gliding alongside flying related ground training, improving access to both activities for those that are located further from VGS sites.</p><p>Volunteers at affected VGSs will be offered opportunities to fill other posts within the Air Cadet Organisation dependent upon their own transferable skills and their personal preferences.</p><p>The Air Cadet Organisation as a National Youth Organisation is not designed to be a recruiting institution for the RAF however it assists in aviation awareness and a proportion of military recruits are former air cadets. The resumption of gliding will support the regrowth of Air Cadet numbers and the reorganisation of the Flying Training offer will continue to provide an enhanced opportunity to our cadets. We therefore do not foresee any change in the proportion of RAF recruits that have enjoyed the opportunities that the Air Cadet Organisation offers.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470393/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T17:36:48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470393/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470393/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Air Force: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Written Statement of 10 March 2016, WS605, what impact assessment his Department carried out on its decision to disband air cadet gliding squadrons in Scotland before making that decision; and what assessment he has made of the effect of that decision on future RAF recruitment.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","31041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470395","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-22","<p>The Democratic People's Republic of Korea's (DPRK) has stated its intention to develop and deploy nuclear weapons and has conducted nuclear and ballistic missile tests in violation of UN Security Council Resolutions. The Department regularly updates its assessments of such programmes, but these assessments are not made public. We remain deeply concerned by the DPRK's actions and continue to urge the country to comply with its international obligations and refrain from any further provocations.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470395/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T16:33:07.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470395/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470395/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","North Korea: Nuclear Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment his Department has made of North Korea's nuclear capability in (a) general and (b) relation to claims by that country that it has developed nuclear-tipped missiles.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","30954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470396","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-22","<p>There are 13,650 British defence personnel permanently based on British military bases overseas. This figure includes those based in Cyprus, Gibraltar, the South Atlantic Islands, Diego Garcia, Germany, Canada, Kenya, Brunei, Nepal and Belize. This figure represents the number of personnel who are stationed at that location. It may differ from the actual number of people working on the base at the time, for example due to deployments. The breakdown of these figures into country and Service is shown below; where countries have five or less personnel, these are rounded to zero and the country does not appear in the table. The Ministry of Defence (MOD) regularly publishes the location figures for both military and civilian personnel, this can be accessed on the GOV.UK website.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Table 1</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>UK Base Country</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Navy</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Army</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>RAF</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Civilian</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>TOTAL</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Germany</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>5,330</p></td><td><p>130</p></td><td><p>2,010</p></td><td><p><strong>7,490</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Canada</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>240</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p><strong>280</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kenya</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>480</p></td><td><p><strong>670</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Brunei</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>140</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>290</p></td><td><p><strong>450</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nepal</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>320</p></td><td><p><strong>340</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cyprus</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>1,530</p></td><td><p>740</p></td><td><p>1,190</p></td><td><p><strong>3,480</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Gibraltar</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>560</p></td><td><p><strong>720</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South Atlantic Islands</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>50</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p><strong>110</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Diego Garcia</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p><strong>40</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Belize</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p><strong>70</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>TOTAL</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>210</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>7,530</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>960</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>4,950</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1,3650</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>(Location of UK regular service and civilian personnel quarterly statistics- 1 January 2016)</p><p> </p><p>The number of defence personnel (military personnel and MOD civilians) on joint operations overseas is approximately 3,600. Joint operations have been defined in this instance as those operations where the UK's contribution is run through the Permanent Joint Headquarters (PJHQ). This includes coalition operations.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470396/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T16:35:31.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470396/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470396/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many defence personnel are based overseas (a) at each of Her Majesty's Armed Forces bases and (b) as part of a joint operation abroad.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","30877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470397","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>A total of 170 responses were received as part of the Submarine Dismantling Project Public Consultation, in respect of interim storage of Intermediate Level radioactive Waste. With the exception of 18 received from instituitions, responses were anonymous and it is not possible to differentiate between residents and businesses.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470397/answer",,,,,"30884","2016-03-21T16:01:01.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470397/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470397/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Nuclear Submarines: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many submissions from local (a) residents and (b) businesses his Department received to its consultation on the Submarine Dismantling Project: site for the interim storage of Intermediate Level radioactive Waste.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","30885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470398","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>Between 1 September 2014 and 15 March 2016 there have been 200 Remotely Piloted Air System (RPAS) strikes in Iraq and 13 in Syria against Daesh targets.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470398/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T15:59:02.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470398/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470398/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Middle East: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many drone strikes have taken place against Daesh targets in (a) Iraq and (b) Syria since September 2014.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","30887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470399","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>Each year UK Armed Forces conduct a considerable number of exercises with their US counterparts, some single service, some joint. The information requested is not held centrally, but is being compiled. I will write to the hon. Member with the information shortly.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470399/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T16:03:57.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470399/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470399/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","USA: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many direct joint training exercises with the US armed forces have been carried out in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","30878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470401","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>UK Defence benefits from considerable engagement with the Australian Armed Forces reflecting the strength of the defence relationship between the two nations. Our records show the number of direct joint training exercises that the UK has carried out with the Royal Australian Armed Forces in each of the last five years is as follows:</p><p>2015-7</p><p>2014-8</p><p>2013-6</p><p>2012-6</p><p>2011-5</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470401/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T16:00:14.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470401/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470401/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Australia: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many direct joint training exercises with the Royal Australian armed forces have been carried out in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","30879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470402","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-17","<p>Stress is recorded as &quot;Mental Disorders&quot; under the World Health Organisation categories of absence, which includes non-stress related absences such as depression.</p><p> </p><p>The proportion of working days lost due to sickness absence for Mental and Behavioural Disorders in each of the last five years is recorded in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Reporting Period</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Absences due to ‘Mental Disorders’ as a Proportion of Total Working Days Lost</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 January 2010 - 31 December 2010</p></td><td><p>18.4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 January 2011 - 31 December 2011</p></td><td><p>19.3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 January 2012 - 31 December 2012</p></td><td><p>19.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 January 2013 - 31 December 2013</p></td><td><p>20.2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 January 2014 - 31 December 2014</p></td><td><p>21.5%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The figures should not be read as being fully related to stress caused absence and it should also be noted that non-work related stress absences would also be recorded here.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Data for the reporting period 1 January 2015 - 31 December 2015 is due to be released at 9.30 on Thursday 17 March 2016 on the gov.uk website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-civilian-sickness-absence-financial-year-201516" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-civilian-sickness-absence-financial-year-201516</a></p><p> </p><p>Information on how many and what proportion of officials in the Ministry of Defence took sick leave for Mental and Behavioural Disorders in each of the last five years will take time to collate and I will write to the hon. Member when the data is available.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470402/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:23:53.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470402/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470402/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Ministry of Defence: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many and what proportion of officials of his Department took sick leave for reasons relating to stress in each of the last five years; and what proportion of total sick leave that leave was in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","30863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470403","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>The Submarine Dismantling Project Response to Consultation Report is due to be published in the middle of this year</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470403/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-21T15:58:33.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470403/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470403/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Nuclear Submarines: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department plans to publish its consultation on the Submarine Dismantling Project: site for the interim storage of Intermediate Level radioactive Waste.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","30883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470404","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-21","<p>A total of 170 responses were received as part of the Submarine Dismantling Project Public Consultation, in respect of interim storage of Intermediate Level radioactive Waste. With the exception of 18 received from instituitions, responses were anonymous and it is not possible to differentiate between residents and businesses.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470404/answer",,,,,"30885","2016-03-21T16:01:01.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470404/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470404/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-14","Nuclear Submarines: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many submissions his Department received to its consultation on the Submarine Dismantling Project: site for the interim storage of Intermediate Level radioactive Waste.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","30884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470406","Department for Education","false","2016-03-17","<p>The Department does not hold the information requested.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470406/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T12:49:08.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470406/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470406/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Schools: Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many police officers are employed by schools on a (a) full-time and (b) part-time basis.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","30895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470407","Department for Education","false","2016-03-22","<p>Under their funding agreement with the Secretary of State, academy trusts must prepare annual financial statements in accordance with the Charity Commission’s Statement of Recommended Practice and the Education Funding Agency’s Accounts Direction, which include requirements for disclosing related party transactions. The financial statements must be externally audited and the auditor must give an opinion on whether they have been prepared on the required basis. The Academies Financial Handbook can be found on GOV.UK at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook-2015</a></p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470407/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T16:53:09.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470407/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470407/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps the Education Funding Agency takes to discover related party transactions which are not disclosed Academy Trust financial statements.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470408","Department for Education","false","2016-03-22","<p>The board of trustees of an academy trust is responsible for monitoring related party transactions. The Education Funding Agency (EFA) reviews related party transactions as part of our assurance and intervention work. Oversight of related party transactions in academies is strong, compared to maintained schools, because of the requirement for trusts to publish details in their financial statements and to have these audited.</p><p>This work forms part of the EFA’s regular assurance and intervention work and does not have a cost associated with it as part of the whole budget for the EFA.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470408/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T16:54:35.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470408/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470408/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the cost to the public purse was of monitoring related party transactions in Academy Trusts in the (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15 financial years; and what the projected cost of such transactions is in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470409","Department for Education","false","2016-03-22","<p>From the 2015/16 Census, 19 trainee teachers had one of their school experiences at a pupil referral unit.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470409/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T17:39:06.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470409/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470409/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Pupil Referral Units: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many trainee teachers have carried out practical teaching experience at pupil referral units.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","30919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470410","Department for Education","false","2016-03-22","<p>Academy trusts are responsible for ensuring that payments to consultants who are connected parties comply with the ‘at cost’ policy as required by the Academies Financial Handbook. The trust’s accounting officer must report in their statement of regularity, propriety and compliance any instances of material non-compliance and the external auditor must provide a regularity report to the trust and Education Funding Agency stating whether these transactions comply with the handbook. The Academies Financial Handbook can be found on GOV.UK at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook-2015</a></p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470410/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T16:57:50.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470410/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470410/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how the Education Funding Agency determines whether related party transactions by Academy Trusts are made at cost in the case of payments to consultants with variable rates.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470412","Department for Education","false","2016-03-22","<p>As at 15 March 2016, 44 Pupil Referral Units have converted to academy status since 2013. These include both, converter and sponsored academy status. All of these academies are currently open.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470412/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T17:11:20.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470412/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470412/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Pupil Referral Units","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many pupil referral units have converted to academy status since 2013.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","30921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470413","Department for Education","false","2016-03-22","<p>The data requested is summarised in the table below. Figures for the year ending 31 August 2015 will be available when the Education Funding Agency (EFA) has completed its reviews for that year in summer 2016.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Year ending 31 August 2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of irregular related party transactions (RPTs)</p></td><td><p>26 (2.4% of trusts with RPTs)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of repayments</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The EFA takes proportionate action when it identifies irregular transactions, on a case by case basis, which can include the recovery of funds.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470413/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T17:36:12.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470413/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470413/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many related party transactions by Academy Trusts were classified as irregular or improper by the Education Funding Agency in each of the last two financial years; and how many such cases resulted in re-payment.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470414","Department for Education","false","2016-03-22","<p>Academy trusts are responsible for ensuring that connected party transactions comply with the ‘at cost’ policy as required by the Academies Financial Handbook. The trust’s accounting officer must report in their statement of regularity, propriety and compliance any instances of material non-compliance and the external auditor must provide a regularity report to the trust and Education Funding Agency stating whether these transactions comply with the handbook. The Academies Financial Handbook can be found on GOV.UK at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook-2015</a></p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470414/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T16:55:34.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470414/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470414/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how the Education Funding Agency determines whether related party transactions by Academy Trusts are made at cost.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470415","Department for Education","false","2016-03-22","<p>Pupil Referral Units (PRUs) are funded by local authorities to offer alternative provision (AP) education. Academies and free schools are unable to open as PRUs. Since 2013, 44 PRUs have converted to become AP academies. Since 2012, 32 AP free schools have opened, with 12 more approved to open in the future.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470415/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T17:10:32.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470415/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470415/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Pupil Referral Units","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many free schools and academies have opened as pupil referral units since 2013.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","30920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470417","Department for Education","false","2016-03-17","<p>The department will draw on evidence from a wide range of sources to determine whether the Special Educational Needs and Disability (SEND) provisions of the Children and Families Act have improved outcomes for children with SEND.</p><p> </p><p>The department published details in March 2015 of our intention to use a combination of local accountability measures, data and analysis and independent inspection to evaluate how the SEND system is performing, which parts are working well and whether outcomes are improving for children and young people. The publication can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/416347/Accountability_Publication.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/416347/Accountability_Publication.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>In May, Ofsted and CQC will begin inspecting local area effectiveness in meeting their responsibilities towards children and young people who are disabled and/or have special educational needs. Inspections will include education, health and care plans.</p><p> </p><p>We will draw on a wide range of statistics on pupils with SEND, including information on educational attainment, absence and exclusions and research into families and young people’s experience of the new system. Statistics on pupils with SEND can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-special-educational-needs-sen" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-special-educational-needs-sen</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470417/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T17:58:06.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470417/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470417/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Special Educational Needs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to evaluate the effect of the introduction of education, health and care plans.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","30971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470418","Department for Education","false","2016-03-17","<p>This is a matter for Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector, Sir Michael Wilshaw. I have asked him to write to you and a copy of his reply will be placed in the House Library.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470418/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T12:48:51.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470418/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470418/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Schools: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many times HM Chief Inspector of Schools has visited a school in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","30972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470419","Department for Education","false","2016-03-17","<p>The number of pupils known to be eligible for and claiming free school meals in schools in Lancashire local authority and Burnley constituency are as follows[1]:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Lancashire Local Authority</p></td><td><p>Burnley Constituency</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>State-Funded Primary Schools</p></td><td><p>14,269 (14.4%)</p></td><td><p>1,811 (22.5%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>State-Funded Secondary Schools</p></td><td><p>8,174 (12.4%)</p></td><td><p>1,032 (21.8%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>State-Funded Special Schools</p></td><td><p>912 (37.3%)</p></td><td><p>121 (49.4%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Pupil Referral Units</p></td><td><p>205 (46.7%)</p></td><td><p>32 (55.2%)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>23,560 (13.5%)</p></td><td><p>2,996 (21.4%)</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>[1] Figures as at January 2015, Source: school census.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470419/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:23:00.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470419/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470419/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Free School Meals: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children are eligible for free school meals in (a) Lancashire and (b) Burnley.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","31001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470420","Department for Education","false","2016-03-17","<p>Local authorities (LAs) spending on education is reported through S251 financial returns on a financial year basis. Prior to 2013-14 data covering spend on top-up funding for SEN was not collected as top-up funding was introduced in April 2013.</p><p>Links are provided below to each of the three available financial years of S251 budget data. Top-up funding for mainstream schools can be found in the High Needs section in each year.</p><p>Budget 2015-16</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/462955/Budget_summary_level__2015_to_2016.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/462955/Budget_summary_level__2015_to_2016.ods</a></p><p>Budget 2014-15</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/357719/Budget_summary_level_2014_to_2015.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/357719/Budget_summary_level_2014_to_2015.ods</a></p><p>Budget 2013-14</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/280926/budget_summary_2013-14.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/280926/budget_summary_2013-14.xlsx</a></p><p>The Department publishes this data as part of the S251 financial collections on the GOV.UK website, usually in the following September for budget allocations.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470420/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-17T16:16:55.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470420/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470420/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-14","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 11 March 2