"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470481","Department of Health","false","2016-03-22","<p>The Department is committed to improving the diagnosis and treatment of rare diseases for all patients, including those with rare forms of kidney disease through implementation of the UK Strategy for Rare Diseases, published in November 2013.</p><p> </p><p>The UK Forum report, Delivering for patients with rare diseases: Implementing a strategy, published on 29 February 2016 includes 51 specific commitments to improve the lives of all those affected with rare diseases. The measures focus on improving diagnosis and early intervention for patients affected by a rare disease.</p><p> </p><p>The UK Rare Disease Forum is working to ensure that specific commitments in the Strategy are embedded in policy development and implementation across the United Kingdom.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470481/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T14:29:29.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470481/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470481/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-14","Kidney Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the implications for his Department's policies on people with rare forms of kidney disease are of the report of the Rare Disease Forum, Delivering for patients with rare diseases: Implementing a strategy, published on 29 February 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","30936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470482","Department of Health","false","2016-03-22","<p>This information is not available in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p>However, NHS England publishes diagnostics waiting times and activity, including performance against the six week target, by clinical commissioning group (CCG) on a monthly basis.</p><p> </p><p>For 2014-15 and 2015-16 this can be found at the following links in the Monthly Diagnostics Commissioner data under the ‘CCG Summary’ tab:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/diagnostics-waiting-times-and-activity/monthly-diagnostics-waiting-times-and-activity/monthly-diagnostics-data-2014-15/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/diagnostics-waiting-times-and-activity/monthly-diagnostics-waiting-times-and-activity/monthly-diagnostics-data-2014-15/</a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/diagnostics-waiting-times-and-activity/monthly-diagnostics-waiting-times-and-activity/monthly-diagnostics-data-2015-16/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/diagnostics-waiting-times-and-activity/monthly-diagnostics-waiting-times-and-activity/monthly-diagnostics-data-2015-16/</a></p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470482/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-22T17:49:33.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470482/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470482/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-14","Health: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people waited six weeks or longer for a diagnostic test in Lancashire in 2015.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","30937"
